Description:
    Generates a complete client-side scaffold from an ActiveRecord model consisting of
    
    * A Backbone.Model
    * A RESTful Backbone.Controller
    * Backbone.Views for showing collection resources and individual resources

Example:
    rails generate backbone:scaffold Ticket

    This will create:
        app/templates/tickets/index.hbs
        app/templates/tickets/show.hbs
        app/stylesheets/tickets/index.scss
        app/stylesheets/tickets/show.scss
        public/javascripts/app/models/ticket.js
        public/javascripts/app/views/tickets/index.js
        public/javascripts/app/views/tickets/show.js
        public/javascripts/app/controllers/tickets-controller.js